  <prompt>
    Replace the hardcoded GUID resolution at `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:30,254` with a stable-ID lookup via `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByIdAsync(WorkspaceOptions.SummarizePlaybookId, tenantId)`. Task 012 already added the typed option + fixed the ADR-018 indexer violation. This task replaces the legacy GUID-based resolution with stable-ID-based, and retires the backward-compat legacy GUID property once consumer migration is complete.
  </prompt>

  <role>SPAARKE platform BFF developer. Expert in workspace file orchestration endpoints + minimal-API DI.</role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:30,254` resolves the summarize playbook via `IPlaybookLookupService.GetByIdAsync(options.SummarizePlaybookId, tenantId)`. Hardcoded legacy GUID removed; the legacy raw-GUID property retired (or marked `[Obsolete]` for stabilization window). Endpoint integration test passes asserting summarize flow end-to-end.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Per spec FR-02 + FR-04 + §1.7 Pattern A. Task 012 fixed the ADR-018 indexer violation but kept backward-compat legacy raw-GUID property. This task completes the migration: stable-ID-based resolution + legacy raw-GUID property retirement. The endpoint at `WorkspaceFileEndpoints.cs:254` is the workspace-side "summarize file" handler used by SpaarkeAi workspace tabs.

      **Refresh (Q&A 2026-06-22 Q1)**: This POML's language was refreshed to match the post-Q1 code reality — stable lookups go through `sprk_playbookid` (immutable opaque ID, GUID-format), NOT `sprk_playbookcode`. See spec.md § Canonical Field Naming for the corrected role table.
    </background>
